comment:
First, I‚Äôm a psychologist and I‚Äôve watched hours of Amber Heard. I had to lay down a foundation of her behavior before I could find out what is mentally wrong with her.  I have NEVER met her or treated her. But I have treated women who have been abused and got them out of their situation and placed them in a women‚Äôs shelter.  I was threatened by their abusers and got them arrested for the abuse and the threats they made to me.  I could tell you some horror stories.  But another time.  I‚Äôve watched hours of Amber‚Äôs videos (the complete videos, not her carefully edited videos), listened to her recordings and watched an hour of her previous deposition in their divorce case, both hers and Johnny‚Äôs.  I believed Johnny did love her, but Amber never loved him, she used him instead. I believe Amber is incapable of loving another person. Why? She‚Äôs a sociopath, a toxic malignant narcissist, has antisocial and borderline personality disorders, she is selfish, entitled, self-centered and she is incapable of remorse, guilt or regret.  She‚Äôs also a pathological, compulsive liar. People with an antisocial personality disorder tend to be deceitful, impulsive. They ignore responsibilities and, in the worst cases, they have no conscience. If that doesn‚Äôt describe Amber, I don‚Äôt know what would. She‚Äôs very calculating, controlling and manipulative.  I NEVER believed her story because she doesn‚Äôt act like an abuse person.  An abuse person becomes an introvert, they are ‚Äúshell shocked‚Äù by the abuse, they become afraid of their own shadow, they jump at any loud noise or when people raise their voice.  Amber is an extrovert‚Ä¶ it was Johnny who showed signs of abuse.  I found this all very disturbing.  You‚Äôve heard the saying that a leopard doesn‚Äôt change its spots. That is true because there are patterns in behaviors that can‚Äôt be ignored in both Amber and Johnny. Johnny would‚Äôve showed signs early if he was an abuser of women and there is no evidence of that.  But there is evidence against Amber with two previous arrest of domestic battery and spent a night in jail.  In one of the videos of Amber recording Johnny‚Äôs behavior, you could see she was trying to instigate a fight with him.  He instead slammed kitchen cabinet doors and never got physical with her.  He was angry but she kept pushing him to lash out at her.  She was trying to set him up and it didn‚Äôt work. He saw she was recording him, and he ended the recording, that was very calculating on her part.  

Now, what I saw in Amber‚Äôs deposition.  First, she kept delaying her deposition three times.  Once she claimed she was at Warner Bros being fitted for her costume for Aquaman.  It was rescheduled and once again she didn‚Äôt show up, claiming she was scared to show up because she was afraid of Johnny.  The Judge didn‚Äôt by her story. They kept setting up a date and she didn‚Äôt show up.  The Judge ordered her to testify the third time and if she didn‚Äôt show up, he would find her in contempt of court and put her in jail.  She didn‚Äôt have a choice.  Her behavior during her deposition was truly bizarre.  She was eating during her deposition; I‚Äôve never seen that ever in a deposition.  It was a delaying tactic; but if she was telling the truth, she wouldn‚Äôt need to delay in her answer. She spoke at times when being questioned, she spoke while she was eating but when it was a question she didn‚Äôt want to answer.  She chewed her food slowly to think of a response.  Johnny‚Äôs lawyer just wanted a yes or no response, she gave this long narrative but NEVER answered the question.  She asked again and got another long narrative.  She asked the question again and her lawyer said asked and answered the question, when she hadn‚Äôt.  But when she talks about the fight on the stairs, she appeared to be in portrayal (acting) mode the aggressor to protect her ‚Äúlittle‚Äù sister.  She became very animated, got a bit aggressive. Amber went into this elaborate narrative, she wanted to be looked at as a hero for protecting her sister against Johnny‚Äôs rage.  That whole narrative was her acting, and not very believable.  I started laughing because it was so calculating, and she was lying.  There is something very wrong with Amber, she‚Äôs too violent and she immediately becomes the aggressor when they‚Äôre fighting.  She lied to her parent‚Äôs, too.  Johnny is a pacifist, and she is domineering and controlling.  Amber is a pathological, compulsive liar.  She was eventually fired from Aquaman 2, Amelia Clarke is now playing her role.  I found the whole scenario suspect as she did this when Johnny was at his lowest point and filed the restraining order just two days after his mother had passed away and the timing couldn‚Äôt have been worse for him. Kick a man when he‚Äôs down so to speak.

comment: Recently, I just got to know more details about Johnny Depp and Amber Heard case, as I was working on a law-based project. This case is quite shocking. I mean, these recordings and opinions of Johnny friends and fans have been COMPLETELY disregarded in the Superior Court trials. I mean, they are not even looking at the facts that many, many people are siding with Johnny, because he is innocent in this case. And being a former DRUG USER, AND NOT A DOMESTIC ABUSER, unlike Amber Heard, why is he being accused of violence and not Amber who has a history of being violent towards other people, and even her previous domestic partner. I think some people really have the audacity to overlook STRAIGHT, TRUE FACTS because they have decided to side with someone. Johnny lost millions of dollars, job opportunities. He had to resign from Warner Bros. productions. He was ousted from Pirates of The Caribbean franchise. It is indeed cruel that Amber is still playing in the WB movie, Aquaman 2, and she hasn't faced any loss even when she went through trials. Honestly, people want to see more of Johnny on screen, and not Amber. I think that WB will be losing money if they let someone else play in Fantastic Beasts and Pirates. In my opinion, even if she wins the case, people will forever look at her as morally and ethically wrong person, and she will lose he reputation in Hollywood film industry. Its a risk for WB that they have ousted Hollywood heartthrob Johnny Depp from its franchises, and has let Amber, a person who is being hated by the world, remain in their movies. Not many people are gonna watch three major movies of WB because WB has completely disregarded people's choice. Its gonna be a difficult time for Johnny with him losing libel case against The Sun, and now the extended date of Defamation Lawsuit (not mentioning the third case). Let's hope for the best and we will forever support Johnny Depp, a kind, generous, handsome, and moral man

comment:
People need to understand this.
Amber has been planning this shit out since the day she met him, since their relationship began. She was in it for the money. She fought him because SHE WANTED AN EQUAL REACTION OUT OF HIM. She wanted HIM to HURT HER. She wanted to MAKE HIM OUT TO BE THE MONSTER FROM THE BEGINNING. But her fighting and abuse didn't get that out of him, she still wanted to use him and get his money, so she made it up and schemed her schemes to go through with her initial plan. She wanted his money but didn't love him, so wanted it through a divorce. For a divorce, she wanted to tell the world he abused her and get out of the situation as the victim and hero. You have to understand that stuff like this doesn't suddenly pop out of a person, it's ingrained in them. 

My uncle has gone through something very similar to this, but on a bigger scale. Nobody was taken to court for it, but that's only because the family didn't want to make a big show out of it.
I won't disclose any names of places. 
So, he married this woman, she was beautiful and youngl and glamorous and just any men's dream. But she was also a goldigging b####. She cheated on him, had another man behind his back, but always expected money and nice clothes from him when he returned home. (He lived abroad) But I guess she wasn't happy with only that, she threatened him with many things, like her own life, constantly, telling him that she'd leave him, or kill herself if he didn't give her this or that. He obliged. 
But it just kept getting worse and worse, she nearly threw herself into a car in the middle of the street in one of her attempts to manipulate him. But you see, she was just a monster, but she had such a pretty face, nobody realised how psycho she really was.
When she was with me, she was just another kind lady. But I guess that was all a mask. She hit and beat him ruthless, bit him, slapped him, was rough and threw stuff at him, tore his clothes off. All types of shit. On top of it all, she was just such a bad wife and partner to him. Would swear and belittle him, threw his clothes out of the wardrobes and made a mess of the house. Never cooked or cleaned up, just left it for the maids. When she came to live with my grandma as a guest for a while, she was absolutely spoilt and acted privileged and above all. But we didn't say anything, we were very conservative and tried our best to be nice. We thought she just had a temper, but she was worse when we weren't around.  The last of her psycho business was when she cut one of her main veins off with a knife and that was the moment my uncle up and left. He literally ran out of the house, packed his suitcase, had enough of it all and caught the nearest plane to Italy and left that day. It was in the middle of the night. I remember lots of screaming, crying, lots of blood on the bedsheets and trails of it on the pavement and you know...the usual when it came to her. We cleaned it up, washed it all and nursed her through it all after he left, and they shortly after got a divorce. It was hard because she kept trying to paint him as the bad guy, that it was his fault that she now couldn't move a limb anymore due to her vein/ artery (Don't remember clearly) She was handicapped and needed us for everything. The maids got tied of her at one point. But we were patient. The moment she returned to her house, she called her mother and framed that my uncle bit her up and abused her. Some people believed her, but most people didn't, because you see...this shit had been going on for a while then and by then, everyone knew she was a few levels of crazy that were above average.

After the divorce, it was chaos. Very hard on us because divorces are frowned upon in my country. Anyway, that was three years ago. He got married again to a sweet woman and has a little newborn now. So I guess he's doing better and is happy now. 

Honestly, when all of this shit was happening, I was younger and didn't think much of it. For all I knew, I was away on a holiday and my uncle's marriage was kinda proving to be very weird. My uncle is a big guy, sturdy and muscly, his ex-wife was short and slender and I didn't really think she could have abused him in any way. But she did, she mentally abused him, manipulated him, controlled him, she was a nightmare that the older I grow, the more I understand. She was sick and twisted and I feel bad for all the men out there who have to suffer through shit like this because society says that it's the men that do the abusing, they don't expect sweet little women to do it, but under the pretty faces, they're just as monstrous. They can be equally scary. Abusers come in all shapes and forms. So don't be fooled.

I just wanted to share this story because it's just one of the many lessons I've learnt from the people in my life that I think many more need to learn from and hear. We're a small (not so small tho) and unknown family from nowhere. We're not celebrities, we're normal people. And we can't afford for our lives to go spiral out like this in the media. But stories like this can really impact someone's life and teach them a lesson. I hope that's what it did. 
Of course, I'm not saying that all men and women are bad, or that all women are manipulative, because no they really aren't. All I'm saying is...don't ignore the red flags when they punch you in the face (no pun intended) and go into relationships...with a little more caution. Thank you for reading this long comment. Have a nice day and stay safe. Always remember that negative people make the safest places, like home, inhospitable. And when that happens, it's time to leave.

comment: I was at a bar one night, saw an ex fling I hadn't seen in two years, we flirted and I went back to her place and we had sex. She talked about us grabbing supper the next day, I said great. By afternoon next day cops came to my house and arrested me for rape... you se, she had a bf even though she told me she was single... and the bf was apparently supposed to be away for a week but came home early, found my condom in the trash, and because she didn't want to look bad, she told her bf i raped her, he told the cops and I'm screwed. She went along with the lie, said I didn't know her and broke into her house. Now, I had been going to therapy for depression for years, since I was 19 as my high school gf had committed suicide after her mom died, and I was pretty lonely and messed up... because I was seeing a therapist every week I would talk about my life, and I told the therapist to release her notes on me from two years prior, as I had talked about having a fling with my accuser and my therapist had it documented... plus, I had txt messages my accuser had sent me after I left her house night and the next morning, asking me to come back over to have sex again, talking about our planned date that night. A cop told me when they showed her proof that she actually knew me and had dated me before, she fell on the floor crying... but the prosecutor still went through with charges. Thankfully the judge threw out the case because it was insane, the bf apologized to me after he learned the truth and broke up with her, but some of the dmg was done. I had become paranoid about dating and being around women, and even though I was vindicated some people will always look at you as a rapist. I was lucky I had multiple ways to prove my innocence, have been married for ten years with 3 kids and another on the way, but the lesson is to not believe people outright. I used to think Jerry Springer crazys were fake... they are not, I've met more than one... be careful.

comment:
Amber Heard; " the reason why I said call 911 was because I WAS (corrects herself) you were ... You had your hands on me" this is a fruedian slip, 
"an unintentional error regarded as revealing subconscious feelings" and this slip of the tongue is common in police interviews and interrogations. The person knows the truth and what happened, it can't be erased from their memory. The subconscious always remembers. Little slips like this, in a police interview usually indicate that the person will remain as a person of interest. Police make the suspect feel comfortable and allow plenty of time for them to talk, the more they talk the more they reveal and the conscious mind struggles to keep two narratives going simultaneously, that's why fragments of the truth will slip out.
